Stepper-Ninja Source-Only Change Log
Date: 2026-04-04

Intent
- This log focuses on source-level changes only.
- The top-level project is treated as the new version.

Added Files (high-impact explanation)
- A full WIZnet ioLibrary tree was added under firmware/ioLibrary_Driver/.
	This brings Ethernet and Internet protocol support sources (DHCP, DNS, MQTT, SNTP, TFTP, HTTP, SNMP).
- New/expanded breakout board and flash programming modules were added in firmware/modules/.
- Quadrature encoder substep implementation and support files were added in firmware/quadrature_encoder_substep/.
- HAL-side feature modules and utilities were expanded in hal-driver/ and hal-driver/modules/.
- New top-level configuration header was added: pio_settings.h.
- Separated BREAKOUTBOARD handling files.
- Added 2 new BREAKOUTBOARD variants (2 and 3) with associated support files.
- Added new USER BREAKOUTBOARD variant with associated support files (breakoutboard_user.c).

Modified Files (with explanation)
- docs/INSTALL.md
	Installation instructions were updated.
- firmware/CMakeLists.txt
	Firmware build configuration was updated.
- firmware/inc/config.h
- firmware/inc/footer.h
- firmware/inc/internals.h
- firmware/inc/main.h
	Core firmware header/configuration layout was revised.
- firmware/modules/flash_config.c
- firmware/modules/inc/flash_config.h
- firmware/modules/inc/transmission.h
- firmware/modules/mcp4725.c
- firmware/modules/serial_terminal.c
- firmware/src/main.c
	Firmware runtime/module integration changed (flash config, transmission, DAC, serial terminal, and main flow).
- hal-driver/install.sh
	HAL installation flow was updated.

Removed Files (with explanation)
- hal-driver/CmakeLists.txt
	Replaced by correctly cased CMakeLists.txt.
- hal-driver/pi_zero2_gui/source/not_fancy.cc
- hal-driver/pi_zero2_gui/utility/image_converter.py
	Legacy pi_zero2_gui implementation artifacts were removed.
- hal-driver/stepgen-ninja.c
	Driver source moved/reworked in current layout.

